7.20	Iced_tea_spoon	Iced tea spoon	An iced tea spoon, also called a soda spoon, is a thin spoon with a very long handle. It is used primarily in the United States, for stirring sugar or other sweeteners into iced tea, which is traditionally served in a tall glass. This is why the spoon has a very long handle.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Iced_tea_spoon.jpg/220px-Iced_tea_spoon.jpg
